<div tiddler="DateFormatString" modifier="JeremyRuston" modified="200510302320" created="200510302320" tags="features">Several [[Macros]] including the TodayMacro take a DateFormatString as an optional argument. This string can be a combination of ordinary text, with some special characters that get substituted by parts of the date:\n* DDD - day of week in full (eg, &quot;Monday&quot;)\n* DD - day of month, 0DD - adds a leading zero\n* MMM - month in full (eg, &quot;July&quot;)\n* MM - month number, 0MM - adds leading zero\n* YYYY - full year, YY - two digit year\n* hh - hours\n* mm - minutes\n* ss - seconds</div>